⁠
YES – of course you can!⁠
⁠
We know how hard it is to quit drinking without the right support. And we know how scary quitting “forever” can sound. ⁠
⁠
You don’t need to commit to quitting before you start the course. You don’t even need to commit to “forever” once you do feel inspired to quit. ⁠
⁠
All we ask is that you come into the course with an open-mind and that you don’t drink before doing any of the work in the course (like watching the videos, reading the manual, doing the workbook etc.). The point of Thrivalist is to get you to a point where you WANT to quit. Where you genuinely don’t see the point in drinking anymore. It’s at this point that you’ll find yourself eager to quit and quitting isn’t difficult.⁠
⁠
We always recommend that anyone on the fence about sobriety commit to a sober-experiement. A no-strings-attached break from alcohol, preferably for 60 days to get a good feel for life without alcohol. ⁠
⁠
If it’s not better sober, you’ve given your body a well-deserved detox and you can always go back to drinking. But we have a sneaking suspicion you won’t want to. And if you do, your drinking will be much more mindful and informed.⁠";}i:30;a:1:{s:14:"comments_count";i:1;}i:31;a:1:{s:11:"likes_count";i:0;}i:32;a:1:{s:4:"link";s:39:"https://www.instagram.com/p/CEusjB9nwrB";}i:33;a:1:{s:5:"image";s:249:"https://scontent-sin6-1.cdninstagram.com/v/t51.2885-15/e35/p1080x1080/118776206_594699364537884_7826329402345223918_n.jpg?_nc_ht=scontent-sin6-1.cdninstagram.com&_nc_cat=100&_nc_ohc=JXLZyvRy4RkAX8dlqWn&oh=504fcb04cc8aad61b9bed429bcdcc110&oe=5F7CEE64";}i:34;a:1:{s:4:"type";s:5:"image";}i:35;a:1:{s:8:"owner_id";i:34879186157;}i:36;a:1:{s:14:"owner_username";s:0:"";}i:37;a:1:{s:14:"owner_fullname";s:0:"";}i:38;a:1:{s:9:"owner_pic";s:0:"";}i:39;a:1:{s:2:"id";s:19:"2391044339726713474";}i:40;a:1:{s:10:"short_code";s:11:"CEusiifnoKC";}i:41;a:1:{s:12:"created_time";i:1599254718;}i:42;a:1:{s:7:"caption";s:108:"🌸🌷

